verses.verse: A Psalm <WH4210> of David <WH1732>. The YY <WH3068> is my shepherd <WH7462> <WH8802>; I shall not want <WH2637> <WH8799>.

He restoreth <WH7725> <WH8787> my soul <WH5315>: he leadeth <WH5148> <WH8686> me in the paths <WH4570> of righteousness <WH6664> for his name's <WH8034> sake.

Yea, though I walk <WH3212> <WH8799> through the valley <WH1516> of the shadow of death <WH6757>, I will fear <WH3372> <WH8799> no evil <WH7451>: for thou art with me; thy rod <WH7626> and thy staff <WH4938> they comfort <WH5162> <WH8762> me.

Surely goodness <WH2896> and mercy <WH2617> shall follow <WH7291> <WH8799> me all the days <WH3117> of my life <WH2416>: and I will dwell <WH3427> <WH8804> in the house <WH1004> of the YY <WH3068> for ever <WH753> <WH3117>.
